Merlin</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugrinkle.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grinkle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/19/01 11:37:03 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1375.topic&index=8>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://sigstuff1.homestead.com/files/Lute_pic.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: why cant we....</span><hr size=1> I agree that stealth makes Archers overpowered.  I have a 16 Ranger with 1 stealth, and I can solo yellows like there was no tomorrow.  Even if I miss my pull shot, as long as I do about 60 dmg on one of the TWO other shots I get off on his run in, I won't die.  I usually have yellows down to 20% before they start hitting me - and I can melee one to death if he starts at 85% reliably.<br>
