</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/ugarnermaceowyne.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Garner MacEowyne</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/20/01 9:46:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1375.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Archers are hardly overpowered</span><hr size=1> The solution to fixing any troubles with assassins in NOT to nerf another class.  Nerfing another class to bring your own up in power is the wrong way to do things IMHO. <br>
<br>
If anything discuss ideas and solutions that will.  <br>
1) Make assassins much harder to detect when stealthed.<br>
2) Make assassins detect others at a much higher rate.<br>
<br>
Use whatever ideas you may come up with to suggest better ways for this to happen.  Keep them simple.  The easier they are to code into the camelot engine the more likely they will be able to implement and kept for consideration.<br>
<br>
Just a quick idea would be to add a few &quot;character levels&quot; to all skill check for assassins, whether for stealthing or detecting.  If stealth seems to be heavy dependant upon character levels this should fix all the problems at a quick glance.   The only issue I can think of is can the game engine handle a &quot;50+ level assassin&quot; skill check?<br>
